<subSubSection id="4A6DE380ABC056F7BD209D8ACB511FEF" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="78B6323589699ABA900EC7C135A05B0E" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="900643B510756E3F4F777F401F4B066F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4A3FE4C8A03C18EE10BEF70E93C7BDFA" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Toxomerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Toxomerus hieroglyphicus" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hieroglyphicus">Toxomerus hieroglyphicus</taxonomicName>
has usually yellow markings in the center of the abdomen. Thus, it should not be included in the present key. However, the study of a dark specimen prompted me to tentatively include this species in case darker specimens might appear with completely black abdomen with lateral yellow maculae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
